          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Ceasefire talks resume </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/hamas-ceasefire-gaza-proposal-egypt-qatar.png" alt="Hamas has agreed to a Gaza ceasefire proposal it received this week from mediators in Egypt and Qatar" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Hamas has agreed to a Gaza ceasefire proposal it received this week from mediators in Egypt and Qatar. Credits: Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hamas has agreed to a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-03-2025-h2-2-new-ceasefire-agreement?source=website" target="_blank">new ceasefire proposal</a> mediated by Egypt and Qatar, offering to release five hostages in exchange for a 50-day truce in Gaza. Israel confirmed receiving the plan and submitted a counter-proposal in coordination with the US.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The ceasefire could coincide with Eid al-Fitr. This proposal follows Israeli ground attacks in Rafah and airstrikes across Gaza, which have resulted in over 900 deaths as per Hamas.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hamas had insisted on adhering to the original agreement and was ready for second-phase negotiations. However, Israel and the US preferred extending the first phase without guarantees of ending the war. Israel accused Hamas of rejecting the extension and subsequently resumed military operations.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
