        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: The Canadian PM claimed a bilateral relationship with the US is ‚Äúover‚Äù in response to Trump‚Äôs further 25% tariffs on car imports.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Canadian PM Mark Carney stressed the need to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-03-2025-h3-3-reduce-dependency?source=website" target="_blank">reduce dependency</a> on the US and claimed that the bilateral relationship with the US is ‚Äúover.‚Äù Carney‚Äôs words resulted from 25% tariffs on car imports. He also claimed that his recent visits to the UK and France were part of his drive to find other partners.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">On Wednesday, Trump announced 25% tariffs on car and car parts imports into the US. This tariff would kill the 1965 Canada-US Automotive Products Agreement. Carney added that Canada would impose retaliatory tariffs and said it should reimagine and retool itself.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">World leaders criticized the tariff and feared it might trigger a global trade war. While EU President Ursula von der Leyen criticized the tariff, Trump threatened an additional tariff on Canada and the EU if they worked against the US.</p>
        </mj-text>
