          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">‚ÄúThe formation of a new government today is a declaration of our joint will to build a new state,‚Äù said Syrian interim President Ahmed al-Sharaa while announcing the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-03-2025-br1-4-transitional-government?source=website" target="_blank">transitional government</a>.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The diverse cabinet of 23 ministers includes representatives from Alawite, Syrian Christian, and Druze communities aiming to create a more inclusive administration amid international pressure. The cabinet excludes a prime minister, with al-Sharaa leading the executive branch.</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Al-Sharaa also established the Ministry for Disaster Management and appointed the leader of the White Helmets, Raed al-Saleh, to lead the initiative. Earlier this month, Syria proposed a constitutional declaration laying the foundation for the interim period governance. </p>
        </mj-text>
