          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üá∏üá∏ South Sudan‚Äôs peace deal has collapsed </strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">South Sudan‚Äôs opposition declared the 2018 peace deal void after First Vice President Riek Machar was arrested by heavily armed forces at his residence in Juba. The arrest, seen as a power grab by President Salva Kiir, follows weeks of escalating violence and breaches of a 2018 peace agreement.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The UN Spokesperson and the head of the UN peacekeeping mission in South Sudan feared a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-03-2025-br2-5-revitalization-of-the-civil-war?source=website" target="_blank">revitalization of the civil war</a> and a dismantling of the peace agreement.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The civil war between 2013 and 2018 saw 400,000 lives lost. The US Department of State requested President Kiir to prevent escalation by reversing this action. Analysts claim Kiir is ensuring his succession by shuffling the cabinet.</p>
        </mj-text>
