          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Why some countries don‚Äôt observe daylight saving time while others do?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/countries-observe-daylight-saving-time-dst-list.png" alt="Countries that observe Daylight Saving Time" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Countries that observe Daylight Saving Time. Credits: TimeZonesBoy</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The US and parts of Europe observe DST, but most countries in Africa, Asia, and South America do not. Over the past decade, most countries have dropped the concept for various reasons, including health concerns. According to the <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-03-2025-f1-6-2023-report-of-pew-research-centre?source=website" target="_blank">2023 report of Pew Research Centre</a>, only ‚Öì of the nations observe this custom.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The time shifts <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-31-03-2025-f1-7-disturb-the-circadian-rhythm?source=website" target="_blank">disturb the circadian rhythm</a> and increase disease severity. These rhythms react to light exposure via our eyes and kick off a hormonal process. Following daylight saving time will affect this, as we would wake to darkness. American Academy of Sleep Medicine correlates daylight saving to social jet lag, which is associated with obesity, metabolic syndrome, cardiovascular disease, and depression.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Countries observing daylight saving claim that adjusting the clock allows them to enjoy more daylight during leisure time and helps conserve energy. The practice started during World War I to avoid using artificial lighting. Politics, government policies, or public opinion often influence the decision to adopt or reject daylight saving time.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
